1621real32_T look1_iflf_binlcpw(real32_T u0, const real32_T bp0[], const real32_T



1622  table[], uint32_T maxIndex)



1623{



1624  real32_T frac;



1625  uint32_T iRght;



1626  uint32_T iLeft;



1627  uint32_T bpIdx;



1628



1629  /* Column-major Lookup 1-D



1630     Search method: 'binary'



1631     Use previous index: 'off'



1632     Interpolation method: 'Linear point-slope'



1633     Extrapolation method: 'Clip'



1634     Use last breakpoint for index at or above upper limit: 'off'



1635     Remove protection against out-of-range input in generated code: 'off'



1636   */



1637  /* Prelookup - Index and Fraction



1638     Index Search method: 'binary'



1639     Extrapolation method: 'Clip'



1640     Use previous index: 'off'



1641     Use last breakpoint for index at or above upper limit: 'off'



1642     Remove protection against out-of-range input in generated code: 'off'



1643   */



1644  if (u0 <= bp0[0U]) {



1645    iLeft = 0U;



1646    frac = 0.0F;



1647  } else if (u0 < bp0[maxIndex]) {



1648    /* Binary Search */



1649    bpIdx = maxIndex >> 1U;



1650    iLeft = 0U;



1651    iRght = maxIndex;



1652    while (iRght - iLeft > 1U) {



1653      if (u0 < bp0[bpIdx]) {



1654        iRght = bpIdx;



1655      } else {



1656        iLeft = bpIdx;



1657      }



1658



1659      bpIdx = (iRght + iLeft) >> 1U;



1660    }



1661



1662    frac = (u0 - bp0[iLeft]) / (bp0[iLeft + 1U] - bp0[iLeft]);



1663  } else {



1664    iLeft = maxIndex - 1U;



1665    frac = 1.0F;



1666  }



1667



1668  /* Column-major Interpolation 1-D



1669     Interpolation method: 'Linear point-slope'



1670     Use last breakpoint for index at or above upper limit: 'off'



1671     Overflow mode: 'portable wrapping'



1672   */



1673  return (table[iLeft + 1U] - table[iLeft]) * frac + table[iLeft];



1674}



1675



1676real32_T look1_iflf_linlcpw(real32_T u0, const real32_T bp0[], const real32_T



1677  table[], uint32_T maxIndex)



1678{



1679  real32_T frac;



1680  uint32_T bpIdx;



1681



1682  /* Column-major Lookup 1-D



1683     Search method: 'linear'



1684     Use previous index: 'off'



1685     Interpolation method: 'Linear point-slope'



1686     Extrapolation method: 'Clip'



1687     Use last breakpoint for index at or above upper limit: 'off'



1688     Remove protection against out-of-range input in generated code: 'off'



1689   */



1690  /* Prelookup - Index and Fraction



1691     Index Search method: 'linear'



1692     Extrapolation method: 'Clip'



1693     Use previous index: 'off'



1694     Use last breakpoint for index at or above upper limit: 'off'



1695     Remove protection against out-of-range input in generated code: 'off'



1696   */



1697  if (u0 <= bp0[0U]) {



1698    bpIdx = 0U;



1699    frac = 0.0F;



1700  } else if (u0 < bp0[maxIndex]) {



1701    /* Linear Search */



1702    for (bpIdx = maxIndex >> 1U; u0 < bp0[bpIdx]; bpIdx--) {



1703    }



1704



1705    while (u0 >= bp0[bpIdx + 1U]) {



1706      bpIdx++;



1707    }



1708



1709    frac = (u0 - bp0[bpIdx]) / (bp0[bpIdx + 1U] - bp0[bpIdx]);



1710  } else {



1711    bpIdx = maxIndex - 1U;



1712    frac = 1.0F;



1713  }



1714



1715  /* Column-major Interpolation 1-D



1716     Interpolation method: 'Linear point-slope'



1717     Use last breakpoint for index at or above upper limit: 'off'



1718     Overflow mode: 'portable wrapping'



1719   */



1720  return (table[bpIdx + 1U] - table[bpIdx]) * frac + table[bpIdx];



1721}

2188real_T rt_roundd_snf(real_T u)



2189{

11681



11682/* Model update function */



11683void LCK_update(void)



11684{



11685  /* Update absolute time for base rate */



11686  /* The "clockTick0" counts the number of times the code of this task has



11687   * been executed. The absolute time is the multiplication of "clockTick0"



11688   * and "Timing.stepSize0". Size of "clockTick0" ensures timer will not



11689   * overflow during the application lifespan selected.



11690   * Timer of this task consists of two 32 bit unsigned integers.



11691   * The two integers represent the low bits Timing.clockTick0 and the high bits



11692   * Timing.clockTickH0. When the low bit overflows to 0, the high bits increment.



11693   */



11694  if (!(++LCK_M->Timing.clockTick0)) {



11695    ++LCK_M->Timing.clockTickH0;



11696  }



11697



11698  LCK_M->Timing.taskTime0 = LCK_M->Timing.clockTick0 * LCK_M->Timing.stepSize0 +



11699    LCK_M->Timing.clockTickH0 * LCK_M->Timing.stepSize0 * 4294967296.0;



11700}
